Interface AdminInterface

All Known Implementing Classes:
AdminService
public interface AdminInterface
The `AdminInterface` defines the business logic and operations that can be performed by an administrator. It provides methods for managing gym owners, gym slots, and user authentication.

  • Method Details

    • approveGymOwner

      boolean approveGymOwner(int gymOwnerId, boolean status)
      Approves or rejects a gym owner based on their unique ID.
      Parameters:
      gymOwnerId - The unique ID of the gym owner to be approved or rejected.
      status - The approval status to set (`true` for approved, `false` for rejected).
      Returns:
      `true` if the operation was successful, `false` otherwise.

    • viewNonApprovedSlots

      List<GymOwner> viewNonApprovedSlots()
      Retrieves a list of all gym owners who are not yet approved.
      Returns:
      A list of `GymOwner` objects with a pending status.

    • changePassword

      boolean changePassword(String userName, String oldPassword, String newPassword)
      Changes the password for a user.
      Parameters:
      userName - The username of the user.
      oldPassword - The current password of the user.
      newPassword - The new password to be set.
      Returns:
      `true` if the password was successfully changed, `false` otherwise.

    • login

      boolean login(String userName, String password)
      Authenticates an administrator for login.
      Parameters:
      userName - The username of the administrator.
      password - The password of the administrator.
      Returns:
      `true` if the login credentials are valid, `false` otherwise.

    • removeGymOwner
